# `oo` — cd into the personal second-brain vault.
# A `cd` can't live in ~/.local/bin/ (subshell scoping), so it's a zsh function here.
# Resolves via the vault-path helper (single source of truth) instead of hardcoding
# a path; --personal always yields ~/Developer/second-brain (a symlink to the iCloud
# vault on the Mac; absent on the VPS, which is work-vault-only). `oow` → work vault.
cd "$(vault-path --personal)"
